# .git-sha is intentionally NOT ignored. `npm run deploy` writes it
# (`git rev-parse HEAD > .git-sha`) and the orchestrator reads it at
# startup as a fallback when RAILWAY_GIT_COMMIT_SHA is empty (which it
# always is for `railway up` CLI deploys). Railway CLI honors .gitignore
# during upload, so adding .git-sha here causes the file to be skipped
# and the drift-detection check silently no-ops in production. The file
# will appear as untracked after each deploy — that's expected.
